and pensions provider in addition aviva has a focus on five markets in europe and in asia the company is focused on the growth markets of china and south east asia aviva is also the second largest general insurer in canada aviva has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index contents  name  history  operations  principal subsidiaries  senior management  sponsorships  references  external links nameedit the name of the company upon its formation in may  was cgnu plc in april  the companys shareholders voted to change the company name to aviva plc an invented word derived from viva the latin for alive and designed to be short memorable and work worldwide in april  aviva announced that it would adopt the aviva name as its worldwide consumerfacing brand and that the norwich union brand would be phased out in the united kingdom historyedit aviva can trace its history back to the establishment of the hand in hand fire  life insurance society in london in  predecessor company london and lancashire fire and life pictured in dublin c  it was created by a merger of two british insurance firms norwich union and cgu plc itself created by the  merger of commercial union and general accident as cgnu in  the aviva name was adopted in july  thereafter most of the group operations except for some strong local brands were carried out under the uniform brand aviva during march  aviva acquired the rac plc breakdown recovery operation for around £ billion in july  aviva greatly increased its presence in the united states by acquiring amerus group a des moinesbased financial services company founded in  in a  billion £ billion deal amerus group was rebranded as aviva usa when the acquisition was completed the company continued to use the norwich union name as a trading name in the uk until  june  when it became formally known as aviva within the united kingdom the launch was supported by a £ million advertising campaign to promote the rebranding one of the most expensive ever in the uk insurance field with the participation of celebrities including bruce willis and alice cooper in june  the company decided to dispose of navigator its australian wealth management business to national australia bank for a million £ million in october  the company decided to focus on its commercial insurance sector and demonstrate its commitment to brokers by launching their find a broker facility using the british insurance brokers association search engine to help them with this endeavour paul whitehouse was recruited to play the part of a successful hairdresser running three salons the message of the campaign focused on business insurance through insurance brokers the closing line of the campaign was were in business to keep you in business in september  aviva completed the sale of rac plc breakdown recovery operation for £ billion to the carlyle group in february  aviva sold its occupational health business to the british support services company capita in july  aviva announced plans to sell or close  noncore businesses in order to simplify its activities and boost shareholder returns as part of the plans aviva announced the sale of its operations in south korea and the closure to new business of its bulkbuying annuity unit in the united kingdom in august  aviva announced that up to  jobs would be lost following a reorganization caused by further turmoil in the eurozone in december  aviva agreed to sell aviva usa corporation to athene holding for us billion £ billion as part of a plan to improve shareholder returns and reduce the groups capital requirements athene subsequently sold the life insurance business of aviva to global atlantic on  april  aviva completed the £ billion allshare takeover of friends life group andy briggs current group chief executive of friends life became ceo of aviva uk life with mark wilson continuing as ceo of the enlarged aviva group in july  aviva froze withdrawals from the aviva investors property trust after announcing a lack of liquidity operationsedit st helens avivas world headquarters in london avivas main activities are the provision of general and life insurance longterm savings products and fund management services the group has around  employees  million customers and aviva investors has £ billion assets under management principal subsidiariesedit united kingdom aviva life – pensions investments life insurance and long term savings formerly norwich union aviva insurance – general insurance aviva investors – fund management formerly morley canada – aviva canada china – avivacofco france – aviva france hong kong india – aviva india indonesia ireland aviva direct aviva health italy – aviva italia holding spa lithuania poland – aviva singapore spain taiwan – first aviva in traditional chinese turkey  avivasa emeklilik vietnam following the completion of friends life group limited in april  friends provident international limited is now part of the aviva group senior managementedit ceo richard harvey retired on  july  his successor was andrew moss the former group finance director moss was paid an annual base salary of £ for his role as chief executive moss resigned on  may  after shareholders voted down a proposed senior management pay deal which would have seen moss increase his basic pay by  despite several years of aviva underperformance john mcfarlane was appointed to the board of aviva plc in september  following the departure of aviva’s ceo andrew moss mcfarlane assumed the role of executive deputy chairman and became executive chairman on  july  on  november  aviva announced that mark wilson had been appointed ceo starting  january  on  september  aviva announced that sir adrian montague would become nonexecutive chairman on the retirement of john mcfarlane at the aviva agm in april  sponsorshipsedit in may  aviva became norwich city football clubs main sponsor in a  television advert starring paul whitehouse they feature a plymouth argyle fc fan who uses aviva car insurance followed by a green army chant it also acquired the naming rights for the redeveloped lansdowne road stadium in dublin ireland and will now be called the aviva stadium in  aviva also took over sponsorship of rugby unions english premiership from guinness the initial fouryear sponsorship deal saw £ million invested into club rugby in july  aviva extended its title sponsorship of the premiership until july  referencesedit  a b c preliminary results  pdf aviva retrieved  march    annual report aviva retrieved  march    a b strategic report pdf aviva retrieved  april    infographic pdf aviva archived from the original pdf on  april  retrieved  april    gary armstrong michael harker philip kotler ross brennan  marketing an introduction pearson education p  isbn  retrieved  september    changing the name of the game the scotsman  may  retrieved  september    ferreiramarques clara  april  aviva scraps norwich union name reuters retrieved  september    aviva heritage events timeline aviva plc retrieved  april    note taken over by commercial union in   cgu and norwich union merge bbc news  february    about us  heritage avivacom retrieved  november    why only avivas directors will be living well london the telegraph  march  retrieved  march    aviva plc retrieved  june    rac history racnewscouk  december  retrieved  april    aviva to acquire amerus for  billion nbcnewscom  retrieved  may    cockcroft lucy  december  bruce willis and elle macpherson star in £ million norwich union advert the daily telegraph london   nab buys aviva to become biggest life insurer sydney morning herald  june   baker rosie  october  aviva launches first ad aimed at business marketing week retrieved  november    aviva completes the sale of rac avivacom  september  retrieved  october    capita announces purchase of aviva uk health reed business information  february  retrieved  june    capita to acquire avivas occupational health business capita plc  february